cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DC. 

The paper is primarily focused on a database system, specifically on optimizing join ordering during query execution. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely category. The paper also heavily relies on reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI. Additionally, the paper introduces a new quality criterion for query execution strategies, which could fall under cs.LG (learning) or cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the performance impact of join order choices, which could fall under cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing).
